FBIS3-32346 "drlat025_m_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 Brazil Cardoso To Resign If Fund Not Approved PY0402140694 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in Portuguese 0900 GMT 4 Feb 94 PY0402140694 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] Leaders of the Brazilian Social Democracy Party, Mario Covas and Jose Serra, support the finance minister's decision to resign if Congress does not approve the establishment of the FSE. Senator Pedro Simon, government leader at Congress, has confirmed that Minister Fernando Henrique Cardoso will leave his position if the FSE is not approved. Cardoso said if his presence at the ministry is creating difficulties, he will leave.
